p: \bSurprised to see me?
\bI guess you would be.
\bWhy would I, Reukra, be the champion?
\bI don't even battle, usually- I just send Taen to do my work.
\bI've spent my life seeking perfection.
\bDeltas... Megas...
\bArmors... Mewtwo...
\bThe entire fiasco with the Unova dragons...
\bIt's all futile. Nothing's worked so far.
\bEverything was strong, but just not strong enough .
\bYou know what the worst part was?
\bHow ridiculous people find our goals to be.
\b"No Pokemon is perfect, it's impossible."
\bAnything can be beaten with a good type matchup, high stats, and appropriate moves.
\bAnd you know what? Maybe they're right.
\bMaybe we've taken the wrong approach to this.
\bA perfect unbeatable Pokemon... it's kind of a stupid thought.
\bAfter all, a combination like Destiny Bond and Shadow Tag can take anything out easily.
\bBut a strategy that can take out a perfect Pokemon can't take out an entire team.
\bI'm realizing this now.
\bHaving one powerful Pokemon doesn't make you perfect. It can still be beaten.
\bBut a team of powerful Pokemon, perfectly synchronized...
\bEach covering each other's weaknesses and increasing their strengths...
\bA team like that could have no weaknesses.
\bIt could be undefeatable.
\bIt could be perfect.
\bAnd now... with that team...
\bI am perfect.
\bSo bring it on, \pn. You want to be the Champion of the Torren Region?
\bBe my guest, but you'll have to beat the person who's beaten the Elite Four before you with their perfect team!
\bGet ready to lose.
pbTrainerIntro(:CHAMPION_Reukra)
$PokemonGlobal.nextBattleBack="Champion"
pbTrainerBattle(PBTrainers::CHAMPION_Reukra,"Reukra",_I("Oh, for crying out loud."),false,0)
\bSo, that's it then.
\bWhat a battle.
\bMaybe...
\bMaybe it seems like I have a little more to learn about all of this after all.
\bWe'll meet again, I'm sure of it.\nAnd my team will be better- and stronger.
\rReukra.
\bSylvan. It's been a while.
\rCongratulations, \pn. I can't believe it.
\rJust recently you were in my lab... choosing your very first Pokemon.
\rAnd now you're the Champion of the Torren League.\nThat's amazing. I'm so proud of you.
\rCome, let's get you registered in the Hall of Fame.
\bSylvan.
\bThank you.
\bFor keeping my secret. For... everything.
\rSure, Reukra. I'd do it for anyone.
\rI just wish I could have helped you more.
\rCome on, \pn, let's go.
pbTrainerEnd
